Ask HN: Why are we hung up on the consciousness question for AGI?
text:
For achieving general AI, why are we hung up on the question of consciousness?

We don't have a way to prove consciousness in humans, let alone AI. For all I know, everyone around me in reality on earth is a NPC bot similar to Westworld, and I am the only conscious person. I have no way to prove otherwise.

Does it matter if an AGI robot is conscious, if it behaves and acts like a normal intelligent human being? Once it passes the "human being like" Turing test, such that there is no way to distinguish a real human from an AGI robot, then the question of consciousness is moot anyway, correct?

Show HN: A game that determines your level of JavaScript ecosystem knowledge
text:
Hi,

Every day you get a short description of 5 npm packages and you have to guess what the projects are. You have three attempts per project. The quiz is reset every noon (UTC) quiz starts on February 5 and runs for 15 days, ending on February 20.

How to read ancient HD when HD controller no longer exists? LIKE THIS
text: When you great grandpa was your age and hard drives were the size of cereal boxes to operate them HD controllers had to manipulate position of disk heads directly. Not like these lazy modern controllers that only request data and hard drives are just operating themselves. So yes, when controller of such ancient drive went to The Land Of Eternal Seeking and there is no schematics at hand you are pretty much left with one simple but hardcore solution https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SwEi7dK3rIA
